Mortuary Baths served as a final stopping point for the deceased royalty before proceeding further to their final resting place, the Qutb Shahi tombs. Built in the style of Turkish and Persian baths, it has separate cisterns for hot and cold water. After the bodies of the deceased have been washed, they were dressed according to the custom and were taken for burial through the Murda gate located at the side of the fort. 
